      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>Harry Flood Byrd (1887-1966) served as governor of Virginia
         from 1926-1930 and United States Senator from Virginia from
         1933-1965.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Press release, 18 December 1955, by Senator Harry Flood
         Byrd, in favor of a referendum calling for a constitutional
         convention to revise and amend Section 141 of the Virginia
         constitution. Section 141 concerned the appropriation of funds
         for educational purposes. The act was approved on 19 January
         1956.</p>
